Some performance numbers from instrumenting the test and profiling it through YourKit on my Macbook Pro.

The current patch spends an average of 1900 ms for 10,002 runs (189 micro-seconds per call).
An equivalent patch that uses file.isDirectory(), file.exists(), file.length() as shown below takes 2080.8 ms for 10,002 runs (208 micro seconds per call).

{code}
 if ((!file.isDirectory() && file.length() != req.getSize()) || !file.exists()) {
          ret = false;
        } else if (dirsHandler != null) {
          ret = checkLocalResource(rsrc);
        }
{code}
